article.description: Azar Swain had a career-high 25 points, including a 3-pointer in the final seconds of regulation to force the first of three overtimes, as Yale got past Siena 100-89 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Swain leads Yale over Siena 100-89 in 3OT
article.linkText: Swain leads Yale over Siena 100-89 in 3OT
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Azar Swain had a career-high 25 points, including a 3-pointer in the final seconds of regulation to force the first of three overtimes, as Yale got past Siena 100-89 on Wednesday night. Swain's 3 with four seconds left in regulation tied the score 72-all and forced the first overtime period. Then, with Yale trailing 80-78 in the first OT, Swain drew a foul and went to the line to sink both free throws, tying it at 80 with 17 seconds left to send the game into the second overtime. Paul Atkinson added 21 points and nine rebounds for the Bulldogs (3-2). Eric Monroe had 14 points, seven rebounds and five assists. Matthue Cotton added 13 points. In the third overtime, a 3-pointer by Cotton put the Bulldogs on top for good, 91-88, with 2:16 remaining. It was the first time this season Yale scored at least 100 points. Manny Camper scored a career-high 22 points and had 19 rebounds for the Saints (2-3). Elijah Burns scored a career-high 22 points and had seven rebounds. Don Carey had 18 points. Yale takes on Penn State on the road on Saturday. Siena matches up against Colgate on the road next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
